### What problem does this feature solve?

In vue, prop validation during development is a great way to catch bugs early. A similar feature would be useful for Vuex mutations.



### What does the proposed API look like?

```javascript
const store = new Vuex.Store({
  state: {
    budget: 0,
    people: {},
  },
  mutations: {
    setBudget: {
      mutation(state, value) {
        state.budget = value;
      },
      type: Number,
    },
    addPerson: {
      mutation(state, value) {
        state.people[value.id] = value;
      },
      type: Object,
      validator(value) {
        return value.id && value.name && value.age;
      }
    }
  }
})
```

